The Oklahoma City bombing, 25 years later: The picture and the pain Aren Almon's daughter became a symbol of tragedy, but mom remembers her girl.
The Oklahoma City bombing stands as the worst act of domestic terror in American history.
"We had looked towards this commemoration for a couple of years, really," Oklahoma City Mayor David Holt said in an interview.
In this Sunday, April 23, 1995 file photo, Aren Almon of Oklahoma City, clutches a teddy bear as she is greeted by President Bill Clinton in Oklahoma City, Okla., after a prayer service for the victims of Wednesday's deadly car bomb attack in downtown Oklahoma City.
In this file photo, a color guard stands at the Field of Chairs during the dedication ceremony of the Oklahoma City National Memorial in Oklahoma City.